    "updated_at": "2025-08-07T18:09:56Z",
    "body": "Even if the detection is adjusted most `git` modules won't work without gitoxide library support.\n\nAs a simple fix it should be possible to catch this specific error and treat a repository as discovered for the purpose of custom modules (perhaps even `require-repo = \"git-sha256\"`), and the `git_status` git-executable backend should work, but other modules will be more complicated depending on the case.\n",
