    "updated_at": "2025-08-07T17:32:53Z",
    "body": "> Even if the detection is adjusted most `git` won't work without gitoxide library support.\n\nIt should be possible to globally change the default `git` provider to the system provided one or perhaps even make a path to a binary specifiable.\n\nIn my view, all this is not the real problem. The problem with Starship here is, that it does not let the user freely decide, what Git binary to use, how to detect a repository, etc.....\n\nIf I could set it all up with workarounds, the way I would've needed it, I'm not sure, if this issue would even exist.\n\nTherefore, I proposed a generic solution, which incidentally is also a workaround for the issue at hand.\nAdd to that the possibility of choosing a custom `git` binary and that's it, no problem, after proper configuration for each comman/module.",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
